  "texts": [
    "There are two fundamental approaches to fine-tuning LLMs (DAS, 2024): Full Fine-tuning (FFT) and Parameter Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT).",
    "FFT involves reconfiguring all the parameters of the model during the training process for a specific task.",
    "This means updating all weights and layers of the model with the training data, creating a new version with improved capabilities.",
    "However, this process may require a significant amount of data and computational resources.",
    "On the other hand, PEFT represents a more efficient form of instruction fine-tuning compared to FFT."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}